{{Pie chart |thumb = right |caption = Religion in Uruguay (2015)<ref>http://www.latinobarometro.org/latOnline.jsp</ref> |label1 = Believer without confession |value1 = 6.3 |color1 = Turquoise |label2 = Atheist, agnostic, none |value2 = 41.7 |color2 = Honeydew |label3 = [[Catholic]] |value3 = 37.4 |color3 = DarkOrchid |label4 = Other [[Christian]] |value4 = 9.9 |color4 = DodgerBlue |label5 = [[Umbanda]] |color5 = Maroon |value5 = 1.9 |label6 = [[Judaism]] |value6 = 0.2 |color6 = Blue |label7 = Other |value7 = 1.0 |color7 = Chartreuse }}
'''[[Irreligion]] in Uruguay''' refers to the [[secularity]] or [[atheism]] in the country. Over 47% of the population is irreligious. [[Uruguay]] is traditionally the least religious country in [[South America]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ine.gub.uy/enha2006/flash/Flash%206_Religion.pdf |title=Flash 6_ Religion |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2012-10-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060923161514/http://www.ine.gub.uy/enha2006/flash/Flash%206_Religion.pdf |archivedate=2006-09-23 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://countrystudies.us/uruguay/43.htm |title=Uruguay - RELIGION |publisher=Countrystudies.us |date= |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/nigel-barber/uruguay-a-secular-utopia_b_1917005.html |title=Nigel Barber: Uruguay: A Secular Outpost Legalizes Abortion |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/142727/religiosity-highest-world-poorest-nations.aspx |title=Religiosity Highest in World's Poorest Nations |publisher=Gallup.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref>
== Secularization in Uruguay == Uruguay is the most [[Secularization|secularized]] nation in all of the Americas with the highest percentage of atheists and agnostics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pitzer.edu/academics/faculty/zuckerman/Ath-Chap-under-7000.pdf|title=Atheism: Contemporary Rates and Patterns 1|publisher=Pitzer.edu|accessdate=2012-10-01|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090612114443/http://www.pitzer.edu/academics/faculty/zuckerman/Ath-Chap-under-7000.pdf|archivedate=2009-06-12|df=}}</ref> 17.2% of the population is atheist or agnostic according to the Uruguayan census.<ref>{{cite book | author = Phil Zuckerman | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tAeFipOVx4MC&pg=PA49&lpg=PA49&dq=atheist+uruguay&source=bl&ots=Kht8EauS2U&sig=cmBpiNiL4bqeNg4DLKHp19ja3es&hl=en&sa=X&ei=LkUCUOOfEcbD0QXNs-yQBw&ved=0CFEQ6AEwBDgK#v=onepage&q=atheist%20uruguay&f=false | title=The Cambridge Companion to Atheism - Michael Martin - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-07-15}}</ref> According to a study by Kauffman, in 2010 47% of the Uruguayan population is defined not religious (of which 24% are atheist, agnostic are 14% and 9% are categorised as sceptical, but neither atheist nor agnostic).<ref name="Atheism to Defeat Religion By 2038">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/nigel-barber/atheism-to-defeat-religion-by-2038_b_1565108.html|title=Atheism to Defeat Religion By 2038|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref> The figures for atheism and irreligion in Uruguay are higher than any other country in the [[Western Hemisphere]]. According to a study by CID-Gallup in 2012, Uruguay is the sixth least religious country in the world (with 29% religious), only behind countries such as the [[Netherlands]] (26%), the [[Czech Republic]] (23%), [[Sweden]] (19%), [[Japan]] (13%) and [[China]] (7%).<ref>{{cite web|title=RELIGION AND ATHEISM |url=http://atheistalliance.org/media/News/RED-C-press-release-Religion-and-Atheism-25-7-12.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Atheistalliance.org |accessdate=2014-10-11 }}{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
== Religious practice in Uruguay == Many Uruguayans nominally describe themselves as [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholics]], but their daily life is usually unaffected by religion.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nJp513dw1oUC&pg=PA77&lpg=PA77&dq=no+religion+uruguay&source=bl&ots=JW3lFChBMa&sig=8m77hbhJiZLqZx1Hn-VXmn0WrLw&hl=en&sa=X&ei=UxgCUNq8HobB0QXToY2YBw&ved=0CFEQ6AEwAzgK#v=onepage&q=no%20religion%20uruguay&f=false |title=Uruguay - Leslie Jermyn, Winnie Wong - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-07-15}}</ref>
