During the war in the 1980s, four Israeli Cobra helicopters backing the attacking force strafed Libbaya and nearby villages, killing a Lebanese soldier.<ref name="LeagueLeague1988">{{cite book|author1=Asian Peoples' Anti-Communist League|author2=Asian-Pacific Anti-Communist League|title=Asian bulletin|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=p4MLAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=23 April 2011|year=1988|publisher=APACL Publications|page=64}}</ref>
==Roman temple== There is a [[Roman temple]] near the town that was called '''Ain Libbaya''' or '''Ayn Libbaya'''. It was classified amongst a group of [[Temples of Mount Hermon]] by George Taylor.<ref name="Taylor1971">{{cite book|author=George Taylor|title=The Roman temples of Lebanon: a pictorial guide. Les temples romains au Liban; guide illustré|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ii8NAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=18 September 2012|year=1971|publisher=Dar el-Machreq Publishers}}</ref>
